rule "ASA_BASE"
when
  (to_string($message.gl2_source_input) == "5ff87a35d9498d01b436d509" ||   
   to_string($message.gl2_source_input) == "60142d77a505c76993ad9016") 
then
  set_fields(
    grok(
      pattern:"%{NU_ASA_BASE}",
      value:to_string($message.message),
      only_named_captures:true
    )
  );
end

source.@value:
rule "ASA_apply_grok"
when
  has_field("vendor_syslog_id") and has_field("vendor_syslog_facility") and
  to_string($message.vendor_syslog_facility) == "ASA" and
  grok_exists(
    pattern: concat(
      first: "NU_ASA_VPN_",
      second: to_string($message.vendor_syslog_id)
    )
  )
then
  set_fields(
    fields: grok(
      pattern: concat(
        first: "%{",
        second: concat(
          first: "NU_ASA_VPN_",
          second: concat(
            first: to_string($message.vendor_syslog_id),
            second: "}"
          )
        )
      ),
      value: to_string($message.message),
      only_named_captures: true
    )
